1912-54     Alan Turing - Father of modern computers
1960        Computing Started
1969        early UNIX at AT&T Bell Labs by Ken Thompson and Dennis Ritchie
1991        LINUX - Linus Torvalds


# Why Operating System?

- Provides set of functions frequently needed by application programs
- KERNEL FEATURES

1. Memory Management
2. Process Management
3. IO devices and Peripheral Management
4. Networking Stack

# ISA
The actual circuitry in the processor of the computer is what "determines" the instruction set.


